# Intelli-Credit Frontend Redesign — Professional Banking SaaS UI

Complete rewrite of the frontend to create a professional, consistent SaaS banking application. Fixes dual-navigation inconsistency, removes all hardcoded static data, connects every page to the FastAPI backend, and applies a distinctive "Institutional Dark" design direction.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **full frontend rewrite** of all 12 pages. The existing Lovable-generated code will be replaced with manually crafted professional components. All ShadCN/Radix primitives are kept but re-styled.

> [!WARNING]
> The backend API endpoints return demo/mock data when Supabase is not connected. The frontend will be wired correctly to all endpoints — actual data flow depends on the backend being running.

---

## Design Direction

**Aesthetic:** *Institutional Dark* — Inspired by Bloomberg Terminal meets modern fintech (Stripe Dashboard, Ramp).

**DFII Score: 12/15** (Impact: 4, Fit: 5, Feasibility: 4, Performance: 4, Consistency Risk: 5 → low)

**Differentiation Anchor:** Deep navy `#0A0F1C` sidebar with luminous teal `#00D4AA` accent — no app will look like this by accident.

### Design System

| Token | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Font — Display** | `Space Grotesk` (Google Fonts) | Geometric, modern, distinctly non-generic |
| **Font — Body** | `DM Sans` (Google Fonts) | Clean, professional readability |
| **Primary bg** | `#0A0F1C` (deep navy) | Institutional authority |
| **Primary accent** | `#00D4AA` (luminous teal) | Action/success signals |
| **Danger** | `#FF4D6A` | Clear risk/rejection signal |
| **Warning** | `#FFB020` | Amber alerts |
| **Surface** | `#111827` | Card backgrounds |
| **Border** | `#1E293B` | Subtle separation |
| **Text primary** | `#F1F5F9` | High contrast on dark |
| **Text muted** | `#64748B` | Secondary information |

### Navigation Architecture (Consistency Fix)
**ALL pages use one consistent layout:** Top navigation bar only. No left sidebar. This eliminates the dual-navigation problem.

- **Login page** → Full-screen split layout (no nav)
- **All dashboard/portal pages** → `DashboardLayout` with:
  - Fixed top navbar: Logo | Page nav tabs | Search | Notifications | User avatar
  - Content area below

